The backend/app directory is intended to contain the core application logic, including models, controllers, and middleware for the Laravel backend. Since this directory will typically contain multiple files, I will create a basic structure with a sample model and controller to get you started.

Here are the contents for the backend/app directory:

1. **Create a Model for the Leaderboard**: `Leaderboard.php`
2. **Create a Controller for the Leaderboard**: `LeaderboardController.php`

### File: /leaderboard-app/backend/app/Leaderboard.php

<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model;

class Leaderboard extends Model
{
    use HasFactory;

    protected $fillable = ['name', 'score'];
}

### File: /leaderboard-app/backend/app/LeaderboardController.php

<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use App\Models\Leaderboard;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class LeaderboardController extends Controller
{
    public function index()
    {
        return Leaderboard::orderBy('score', 'desc')->get();
    }

    public function store(Request $request)
    {
        $request->validate([
            'name' => 'required|string|max:255',
            'score' => 'required|integer',
        ]);

        return Leaderboard::create($request->all());
    }
}

### Note
You may need to create additional files for middleware, requests, or other models as your application grows. The above files provide a basic structure to get started with your leaderboard application.